         <abstract id="aspace_1f6f245997500925fdb686306a0a621e">Sermons, scrapbooks, notes, and writings document the work of an Episcopal clergyman in New England during the last part of the 19th century and the first two decades of the 20th century. Otis Olney Wright was an Episcopal clergyman. He served St. John's Church in Sandy Hook, CT from 1891 to ca. 1917.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname source="local">
               <part>Wright, Otis Olney</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
